In a press briefing, White House Press Secretary Josh Earnest answered questions about various topics including the President's views on the Republican debate, the Iran deal, Guantanamo Bay, and the migrant ship tragedy. Earnest stated that the President does not have a rooting interest in the debate, but will be interested in the arguments presented. He defended the Iran deal, arguing that killing the deal would lead to military action against Iran, and that diplomacy is the best way to prevent Iran from obtaining a nuclear weapon. Earnest also mentioned that the President is committed to closing the Guantanamo Bay detention facility and that a plan is being worked on. On the migrant ship tragedy, he expressed the administration's concern and stated that they are working to find a political resolution in Syria to reduce the violence and the humanitarian crisis.